Written evidence from Police and Crime Commissioner, Thames Valley [CST0038][bold]Response to Public Administration Select Committee request for evidence on Crime Statistics[bold] [bold]In response to questions raised by the Chairman of [bold]PASC[bold] in his letter of [bold]6[bold]th[bold] December 2013[bold], Thames Valley PCC’s response is as follows:[bold]What, if any[bold],[bold] targets do you set for your police force? What impact do you think this has on police recording practices?[bold]For 2013-14, 
[normal]I have 
[normal]set five
[normal] ‘headline’ targets. Two of these (
[normal]Burglary Dwelling and Violence against the Person) are Crime Reduction Targets. The other three are detection targets (Burglary Dwelling, Rape Offences, and Violence against the Person with Injury). 
